msgid "If you want to host an event without selling tickets, you can arrange it with WPEventin. Woocommerce is not mandatory in this scenario. In that case, simply skip enabling the “Sell on Woocommerce” option. On the other hand, you can enable selling tickets and put the event ticket price as zero(0), then it will act as a free event and your customers don't have to pay for that event. In this way, you can skip the price of the tickets."
msgstr ""

#: dist/timetics/utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:336
#: utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:336
msgid "I am getting a 404 error. What to do now?"
msgstr ""

#: dist/timetics/utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:339
#: utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:339
msgid "You can get a 404 Not Found error for many reasons in WordPress. However, the most common reason for the 404 error is page permalink. In order to solve the permalink error, please login to your WordPress dashboard and click on settings. Then from permalink, select “ Post name” as permalink structure and save the settings. Solution key wp-admin -> settings -> permalink -> Post name -> Save Changes."
msgstr ""

#: dist/timetics/utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:351
#: utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:351
msgid "Does Eventin support different page builders?"
msgstr ""

#: dist/timetics/utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:354
#: utils/pro-awareness/pro-awareness.php:354
msgid "Yes. Eventin supports different page builders like DIVI builder, Visual Composer and Elementor page builder. You can use a shortcode for DIVI builder and Visual Composer. And the plugin has 15+ dedicated widgets for the Elementor page builder. Most of the widgets are FREE to use. However, <a href=\"https://themewinter.com/eventin/\" target=\"_blank\">Eventin PRO</a> will be required for a few specific widgets."
msgstr ""

